    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mourning a Relative, and an Estate</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steven B Frakt letter on Stanley Herz's Sept 21 article questions his attack on estate tax</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Stanley Herz (Op-Ed, Sept. 21) complains that because ''the stock market took off,'' his mother-in-law's estate must pay more than a third of everything over $675,000 in taxes. I'm a little confused. Are we supposed to feel upset about the tax or upset that the stock market has boomed?</p>
        <p>STEVEN B. FRAKT  Princeton, N.J., Sept. 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
